In [6]:
LABEL_COL = "PINCP"
SENSITIVE_COL = "SEX"
#SENSITIVE_COL = "RAC1P"

def split_X_Y_S(data, ignore_cols=None, unawareness=False) -> tuple:
    ignore_cols = ignore_cols or []
    ignore_cols.append(LABEL_COL)
    if unawareness:
        ignore_cols.append(SENSITIVE_COL)
    
    feature_cols = [c for c in data.columns if c not in ignore_cols]
    
    return (
        data[feature_cols].to_numpy(),    # X
        data[LABEL_COL].to_numpy(),       # Y
        data[SENSITIVE_COL].to_numpy(),   # S
    )
In [7]:
X_train, y_train, s_train = split_X_Y_S(train_data)
X_val, y_val, s_val = split_X_Y_S(val_data)
X_test, y_test, s_test = split_X_Y_S(test_data)

In [12]:
from hpt.tuner import ObjectiveFunction, OptunaTuner

obj_func = ObjectiveFunction(
    X_train=X_train, y_train=y_train, s_train=s_train,
    X_val=X_val, y_val=y_val, s_val=s_val,
    X_test=X_test, y_test=y_test, s_test=s_test,
    hyperparameter_space=HYPERPARAM_SPACE_PATH,
    eval_metric=PERFORMANCE_METRIC,
    other_eval_metric=FAIRNESS_METRIC,
    threshold=0.50,
    alpha=0.75,  # this just influences the plot and how to choose the best trial, not optimization
)
In [13]:
# Create storage folder to save local optuna db
Path("storage").mkdir(exist_ok=True)

# Create tuner object
tuner = OptunaTuner(
    objective_function=obj_func,
    study_name=f"{HYPERPARAM_SPACE_PATH.name}-study-{RANDOM_SEED}", # Choose a name for this Study
    storage='sqlite:///storage/optuna-studies.db', # Choose a path to the DB (example using a local sqlite DB)
    load_if_exists=False,
)
